# Matching UI

When building or editing UI anywhere in FarmBondhu, match the **workspace/module** the page belongs to — all routes, roles, and user types. Do not drop in generic or off-theme colors.

## Global color policy

- **Never use purple or violet:** no Tailwind `purple-*`, `violet-*`, or ad-hoc hex like `#8B5CF6`, `#9333EA`, `#A855F7`, or `hsl(262, …)`.
- **Default:** identify the module from the route or sidebar layout, then use that module’s tokens — do not invent a new accent.
- Prefer [`ICON_COLORS`](frontend/src/lib/iconColors.ts) and module theme files over raw Tailwind color classes.
- Shared shadcn neutrals (`border-border`, `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`) are fine everywhere; **accents** must be module-matched.

